---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";

const tocLink =
  "block text-[0.75rem] max-[760px]:text-[0.88rem] text-muted no-underline py-[4px] border-b border-transparent transition-colors duration-200 hover:text-ink";
const docSection = "mb-[48px] scroll-mt-[100px]";
const docH2 =
  "font-ui font-extrabold text-[1.3rem] max-[760px]:text-[1.2rem] tracking-[-0.5px] text-white mb-[14px] pb-[10px] border-b border-line2";
const docP = "text-[0.8rem] max-[760px]:text-[0.92rem] text-[#6a7a8a] leading-[1.85] mb-[14px]";
const docList = "list-none mb-[14px]";
const docItem =
  "flex gap-[8px] text-[0.8rem] max-[760px]:text-[0.92rem] text-[#6a7a8a] py-[4px] leading-[1.7] before:content-['›'] before:text-cyan before:shrink-0";
const inlineLink = "text-cyan hover:underline";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Sort & Visualize"
  description="Sort & Visualize privacy policy: what data we collect, how cookies and local storage are used, and the third-party services (including advertising) that may run on this site."
  activePath="/privacy"
>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Legal" glow="transparent">
    <Fragment slot="title"><em class="text-cyan not-italic">Privacy</em> Policy</Fragment>
    <div class="text-[0.68rem] text-muted tracking-[1px]">Last updated: June 2026</div>
  </PageHero>

  <div class="max-w-[720px] mx-auto px-[40px] pt-[60px] pb-[100px] max-[980px]:px-[24px] max-[760px]:px-[18px]">
    <div class="bg-panel border border-line2 rounded-[10px] p-[24px] mb-[48px]">
      <div class="text-[0.62rem] max-[760px]:text-[0.75rem] tracking-[2px] uppercase text-cyan mb-[14px]">Table of Contents</div>
      <a href="#overview" class={tocLink}>1. Overview</a>
      <a href="#data" class={tocLink}>2. Data We Collect</a>
      <a href="#cookies" class={tocLink}>3. Cookies & Local Storage</a>
      <a href="#third-party" class={tocLink}>4. Third-Party Services</a>
      <a href="#children" class={tocLink}>5. Children's Privacy</a>
      <a href="#changes" class={tocLink}>6. Changes to This Policy</a>
      <a href="#contact-priv" class={tocLink}>7. Contact</a>
    </div>

    <section id="overview" class={docSection}>
      <h2 class={docH2}><em class="text-cyan not-italic">1.</em> Overview</h2>
      <div class="bg-[rgba(0,255,200,0.04)] border border-[rgba(0,255,200,0.15)] rounded-[8px] p-[16px_18px] mb-[16px]">
        <p class="text-[0.8rem] text-ink leading-[1.85] mb-0">
          The Sort &amp; Visualize application itself runs entirely in your browser — we operate
          <strong>no user accounts, no database, and no server-side processing</strong> of your
          information. We do, however, rely on third-party services such as Google AdSense
          (advertising) and Google Fonts, which may use cookies and collect limited technical data as
          described below.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class={docP}>
        This Privacy Policy explains what data is involved when you use Sort &amp; Visualize, including the role of
        cookies and third-party providers. We are committed to transparency and to keeping our own data
        collection to a minimum.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="data" class={docSection}>
      <h2 class={docH2}><em class="text-cyan not-italic">2.</em> Data We Collect</h2>
      <p class={docP}>
        We do not directly collect, store, or transmit personal information on our own servers.
        Specifically, Sort &amp; Visualize itself:
      </p>
      <ul class={docList}>
        <li class={docItem}>Does not ask for your name, email, or contact information to use the tool</li>
        <li class={docItem}>Does not log your IP address on any server we operate</li>
        <li class={docItem}>Does not require user accounts or profiles</li>
        <li class={docItem}>Does not send your sorting data, array inputs, or algorithm selections to any server</li>
      </ul>
      <p class={docP}>
        All sorting computation (algorithms, animations, audio) happens locally in your browser, and
        your activity within the tool never leaves your device. However, third-party services we embed
        — in particular our advertising partner (Google AdSense) and Google Fonts — may independently
        collect limited technical data such as your IP address, device and browser information, and
        interaction signals. This is covered in sections 3 and 4 below.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="cookies" class={docSection}>
      <h2 class={docH2}><em class="text-cyan not-italic">3.</em> Cookies & Local Storage</h2>
      <p class={docP}>
        Cookies are small text files stored by your browser. Sort &amp; Visualize does not set its own cookies for
        tracking or profiling. However, third-party services running on this site — most notably Google
        AdSense — may set and read cookies on your device to deliver and measure advertising.
      </p>
      <p class={docP}>
        Specifically, Google and its partners use cookies (including the DoubleClick cookie) to serve
        ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites. You can opt out of personalised
        advertising by visiting
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" class={inlineLink}>Google Ads Settings</a>, and you
        can learn more about how third-party vendors use cookies at
        <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" class={inlineLink}>www.aboutads.info</a>. Your browser may
        also cache static assets (HTML, CSS, fonts) for performance — this is standard behaviour and
        contains no personal data.
      </p>
      <p class={docP}>
        When you first visit Sort &amp; Visualize, a cookie consent banner will appear. You may accept or reject
        non-essential cookies. Your preference is stored in your browser's localStorage under the key
        "sortlab-consent". Essential cookies required for the site to function are always active.
        Advertising cookies (used by Google AdSense) are only activated after you provide consent.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="third-party" class={docSection}>
      <h2 class={docH2}><em class="text-cyan not-italic">4.</em> Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p class={docP}>
        <strong class="text-ink">Advertising (Google AdSense).</strong> We use Google AdSense to display
        advertisements that help keep Sort &amp; Visualize free. Google is a third-party vendor that uses cookies
        and similar technologies to serve ads based on your visits to this and other sites. Google's use
        of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on your visits. You
        may opt out of personalised advertising via
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" class={inlineLink}>Google Ads Settings</a>. For
        details on how Google handles data in its products, see the
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" class={inlineLink}>Google Privacy &amp; Terms</a>
        page.
      </p>
      <p class={docP}>
        <strong class="text-ink">Advertising (Google AdSense).</strong> This site participates in Google
        AdSense, an advertising program operated by Google LLC. Google AdSense uses cookies (including
        the DoubleClick cookie) and web beacons to serve advertisements based on your prior visits to
        this and other websites. These cookies allow Google and its partners to serve ads based on your
        browsing history. You may opt out of personalised advertising at any time by visiting
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" class={inlineLink}>Google Ads Settings</a> or
        <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices" class={inlineLink}>www.aboutads.info/choices</a>.
        For more information about how Google uses data, visit
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" class={inlineLink}>Google's Privacy & Terms page</a>.
      </p>
      <p class={docP}>
        <strong class="text-ink">Fonts.</strong> Sort &amp; Visualize loads typefaces from Google Fonts
        (fonts.googleapis.com), so your browser requests these files from Google's servers. Google's
        privacy policy applies to that interaction.
      </p>
      <p class={docP}>
        Aside from Google AdSense and Google Fonts, we do not knowingly load other analytics platforms
        or tracking services. We have no control over the data practices of these third-party providers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="children" class={docSection}>
      <h2 class={docH2}><em class="text-cyan not-italic">5.</em> Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p class={docP}>
        Sort &amp; Visualize is intended for a general audience — primarily students, educators, and developers —
        and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from
        children. Because advertising networks such as Google AdSense may use cookies, we do not
        encourage use by children under 13 without the involvement of a parent, guardian, or teacher. If
        you believe a child has provided personal data through any third-party service on this site,
        please contact us so it can be addressed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="changes" class={docSection}>
      <h2 class={docH2}><em class="text-cyan not-italic">6.</em> Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p class={docP}>
        If we ever change our privacy practices, we will update this page and revise the "Last updated"
        date at the top. We will always maintain a commitment to minimal data collection and full
        transparency.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact-priv" class={docSection}>
      <h2 class={docH2}><em class="text-cyan not-italic">7.</em> Contact</h2>
      <p class={docP}>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out via our
        <a href="/contact" class={inlineLink}>Contact page</a>. We will respond to all privacy inquiries
        promptly.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
